+# Software Test Description (STD)
+
+## Feature: Windows Guest Agent OS/Hostname Info Display
+
+**STP Reference:** [stps/7.md](/home/fedora/thesis/stps/7.md)
+**Jira ID:** CNV-61262 (Feature), CNV-56888 (Bug Fix)
+**Generated:** 2026-02-23
+**PR:** [kubevirt/kubevirt#14232](https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/pull/14232)
+
+---
+
+## Summary
+
+This STD covers the bug fix for Windows VMs incorrectly showing "Guest Agent Required" for OS/hostname information even when qemu-guest-agent is running. The fix ensures `domain.Status.OSInfo` is not empty when the guest agent reports data.
+
+Tests verify:
+- VMI status correctly reflects Windows OS information reported by the guest agent
+- VMI status correctly reflects the Windows hostname
+- Guest agent information persists and remains correct after a guest reboot
+- Guest agent information appears dynamically when the agent service transitions from stopped to running
+
+---
+
+## Test Files
+
+### File: `tests/virt/guest_agent/test_windows_guest_agent_os_info.py`
+
+```python
+"""
+Windows Guest Agent OS/Hostname Info Display Tests
+
+STP Reference: stps/7.md
+Jira: CNV-61262 / CNV-56888
+
+Verifies that Windows VMs correctly display OS and hostname information
+via the guest agent, addressing the bug where domain.Status.OSInfo was
+sometimes empty despite the agent running.
+"""
+
+import pytest
+
+
+class TestWindowsGuestAgentOSInfo:
+    """
+    Tests for Windows guest agent OS and hostname info display in VMI status.
+
+    Markers:
+        - virt
+        - high_resource_vm
+
+    Preconditions:
+        - Running Windows VM with qemu-guest-agent installed and running
+        - virtio-serial driver installed for guest-host communication
+        - VM is SSH accessible
+    """
+
+    def test_vmi_os_info_matches_windows_os(self):
+        """
+        Test that VMI guestOSInfo matches the actual Windows OS information.
+
+        Steps:
+            1. Compare VMI status guestOSInfo fields against OS information
+               queried directly from the Windows guest via SSH
+
+        Expected:
+            - VMI guestOSInfo fields (name, version, kernelRelease, prettyName,
+              versionId, kernelVersion, machine, id) match the values reported
